I'm more than a little baffled by the harsh reviews I've been reading here over the past week, a.k.a.
the first week that Merchant has been open.
I went with a friend I was visiting in Madison just before Christmas for dinner and drinks and had a wonderful time.
I love the interior.
The grocery, which I understand will be opening soon, looks awesome on the wall across from the bar.
Even if you don't plan on buying any groceries here, it's cool to browse all the ingredients that they use in the food you'll be eating.
The old school bodega gates covering the grocery when it's closed are a nice touch.
We shared a lot of the food we ordered to get a chance to try multiple dishes and I highly recommend eating family style.
We started with cocktails of course (I'm a fan of the Loretto Flower) and the Chicory salad, both really great.
Next we had what ended up being my favorite part of the meal, the Toasts.
Loved the hugh piece of toast with truffled white bean and prosciutto.
For $3 each, we tried them all and apparently they change constantly so I'll be back to try the new additions.
For dinner we ordered the shrimp with grits and the beef bourguignon.
The fun part about ordering these dishes and I'm assuming most dishes at Merchant, is the surprises you get when your food comes.
The menu descriptions are very vague (a good thing) so when the shrimp showed up sitting on a pork belly, we were so excited and it did not disappoint.
Obviously, you can always ask the server what is in each dish.
We ate for a good amount of time at a slow pace by our own choice.
We were never without drinks, but our server wasn't always bugging us to see how we were doing.
It's not a huge place, so we never had trouble getting his attention if we had to.
He knew everything about the menu and wasn't at all pretentious like another reviewer suggested.
By about 10PM the restaurant turned more into a bar scene so we settled our tab and moved on to the bar where we had a few more cocktails and a couple local beers.
Everyone was really great, drinks came at a decent pace (again, this place is now just over one week new!
) and the crowd was a decent mix of young and old.
I'm excited to return for dinner and hopefully for lunch some day soon, the sandwich menu sounds really interesting.
Great food, great drinks, great staff and great atmosphere.
I'd hang out here every night if I had the chance.
I highly recommend Merchant and will be returning often.

