Here's why I'm giving it 4 stars: Went there to "grab" a tasty treat with a limited time frame.
Their sandwich area was closed, but the hostess immediately offered to go back and check to see if they could whip up a to-go sandwich order for me.
They even ushered me to a table and poured me a glass of water while I waited for my take-out order.
I picked the procuitto and arugula sandwich - very good, yet light.
